## 4. Theming & Responsiveness Utilities

### Responsive Breakpoints

Access standardized breakpoints via `context.theme`:

```dart
final bp = context.theme.breakpoints;
final width = MediaQuery.sizeOf(context).width;

// Standard Logic
if (width < bp.sm) return MobileLayout();
if (width < bp.lg) return TabletLayout();
return DesktopLayout();
```

### Interactive State Styling (`FWidgetStateMap`)

When creating custom styles (via CLI), use `FWidgetStateMap` to handle interactions without `setState`:

```dart
// In lib/theme/my_style.dart
style: FButtonStyle(
  backgroundColor: FWidgetStateMap({
    WidgetState.disabled: Colors.grey,
    WidgetState.hovered: Colors.blueAccent,
    WidgetState.any: Colors.blue, // Default
  }),
)
```

### Theme Extensions

Access custom theme properties defined in your app:

```dart
// Extension on BuildContext
final brandColor = context.theme.extension<BrandColors>()?.primary;
```

