## 5. Decision Matrix: CLI Style vs. Direct Usage

This protocol prevents codebase pollution while ensuring maintainability.

| Scenario | Approach | Rationale |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Reusable Component** (e.g., `PrincepsBadge`) | **CLI Style** (`lib/theme/badge_style.dart`) | Centralizes styling, ensures consistency across screens. |
| **State-Dependent Styling** (Hover/Press) | **CLI Style** | Allows use of `FWidgetStateMap` for declarative interactivity. |
| **One-off Layout** (e.g., Login Form Card) | **Direct** (`FCard(style: context.theme.cardStyle.copyWith(...))`) | Avoids creating a global style file for a single usage. |
| **Structural Grouping** (e.g., TileGroup) | **Direct** | Structure rarely needs a custom global theme; standard theme suffices. |
| **Dynamic Styling** (Color based on API data) | **Direct** (`copyWith`) | CLI styles are static; data-driven styles must be runtime. |

